{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/creating-a-custom-keyboard","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is an app extension that you ship together with your app. Once enabled in Settings, it can replace the native system keyboard by selecting it with the bottom-leading 🌐 key while typing."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Keyboard extensions are the only kind of apps that can be used directly with other apps in iOS. By extending your app’s features for use in a custom iOS keyboard, your users will be able to use them in any app that supports text input.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"How do I create a custom keyboard?","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"How-do-I-create-a-custom-keyboard"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can add a custom keyboard to any iOS app, from Xcode’s “File > New > Target…” menu option. This will add a keyboard extension to your app and make it possible to switch to that keyboard while typing in any app."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"this article"}],"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"this article","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/creating-a-custom-keyboard"},{"text":" for a guide on how to create a custom keyboard extension from scratch, and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/library\/archive\/documentation\/General\/Conceptual\/ExtensibilityPG\/CustomKeyboard.html"},{"text":" for more extensive information.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"What can a custom keyboard be used for?","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"What-can-a-custom-keyboard-be-used-for"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A custom keyboard can be used to provide custom autocomplete & spell-checking functionality, more sophisticated text analysis, AI-based features, etc. The possibilities are endless, but Apple’s native APIs are very limited by default.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"What can a custom keyboard do?","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"What-can-a-custom-keyboard-do"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A custom keyboard can render any user interface and resize the keyboard area to fit its content. It uses a ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"document proxy"}]},{"text":" to read and write text from and to the currnetly active text field, and can require Full Access to enable capabilities like network access.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"What can a custom keyboard NOT do?","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"What-can-a-custom-keyboard-NOT-do"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s native APIs are very limited, and basically just lets you read and write text in limited ways. Some things are however not possible. For instance, a keyboard can’t draw outside its bounds, and is memory capped at ~70 MB. Apple also doesn’t provide a keyboard view."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Why should I use KeyboardKit?","type":"heading","anchor":"Why-should-I-use-KeyboardKit","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit extends Apple’s native APIs and adds more features to make it a easier to create amazing custom keyboards. KeyboardKit also has a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardView"},{"text":" that renders a native-looking, fully customizable keyboard with just a few lines of code.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Why should I use KeyboardKit Pro?","type":"heading","anchor":"Why-should-I-use-KeyboardKit-Pro","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit Pro extends KeyboardKit with pro features, like support for 75+ locales, autocomplete, dictation, fonts, an emoji keyboard, clipboard management, themes, etc.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Further Reading","type":"heading","anchor":"Further-Reading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"this article"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/creating-a-custom-keyboard","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"this article"},{"type":"text","text":" for a guide on how to create a custom keyboard extension from scratch, and "},{"isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"this article","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/library\/archive\/documentation\/General\/Conceptual\/ExtensibilityPG\/CustomKeyboard.html","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"this article"},{"type":"text","text":" for more extensive information."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See KeyboardKit’s "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Getting-Started-Article","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" guide for further reading on how KeyboardKit can help you create a custom keyboard from scratch."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Developer-Data-Syncing","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Developer-Debugging","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Developer-dSYMs","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Developer-Experiments","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Developer-Memory-Management"],"title":"Essentials"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/keyboa